  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite its absence from high-visibility platforms and citation metrics, \"Dies irae,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021, reflects a distinct potential for engagement through its commercial availability on major platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads. This suggests a foundational interest that may grow as discussions evolve.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Dies irae,\" released by Leuven University Press in 2021, presents a profound scholarly effort that, while currently showing no citations, indicates a strong commercial linkage within the academic and literary community. The availability of the work on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads highlights its potential reach and accessibility, which could set the stage for future engagement and discourse.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The lack of external citations, social media mentions, or other public discourse metrics may suggest a period of development for this work rather than a lack of significance. The commercial presence indicates that there is an audience that might be receptive to its content, and as awareness grows, the discourse surrounding \"Dies irae\" could eventually emerge on platforms that facilitate academic and community discussions.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Even without direct public engagement metrics, the work's strength lies in its availability as a scholarly output. By being included in reputable commercial platforms, \"Dies irae\" has the potential to stimulate interest among both academics and general readers alike, possibly leading to discussions that enhance its visibility and impact in the future.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">As we look ahead, fostering community dialogue around \"Dies irae\" will be critical. Engaging with potential readers and researchers through academic events and conversations may facilitate a greater understanding of its contributions, thereby enhancing its scholarly footprint and encouraging a more vibrant dialogue in the years to come.</p>",
